HEADWORD: Melchite
<hw>Mel"chite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Heb.
<ets>melek</ets> king.]</ety> <fld>(Eccl. Hist.)</fld> <def>One of a
sect, chiefly in Syria and Egypt, which acknowledges the authority of
the pope, but adheres to the liturgy and ceremonies of the Eastern
Church.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

